Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Mussel Inn (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the proprietor of the music venue the Mussel Inn (pictured) in Onekaka built tables strong enough for up to eight people to dance on?

entry.title: Fabrizio Dori (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Fabrizio Dori wants his comic book Il dio vagabondo to bring attention to an ancient Greek view of death?

entry.title: Paul Nunn (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Paul Nunn worked as a climbing double for Sean Connery on the film Five Days One Summer?

entry.title: PHerc. Paris. 4 (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that it took a particle accelerator and machine-learning algorithms to extract the charred text of PHerc. Paris. 4 without unrolling it?

entry.title: Cecelia Hall (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that American mezzo-soprano Cecelia Hall portrayed the lead male role in Mozart's Ascanio in Alba?

entry.title: Matt Rempe (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that New York Rangers forward Matt Rempe is the first ice hockey player to make his National Hockey League debut in an outdoor game?

entry.title: Weise's law (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Weise's law was first proposed as a way to explain why cognates differ unexpectedly in ancient Greek and Sanskrit?

entry.title: William Kuykendall (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Oregon state senator William Kuykendall was a physician who founded the first hospital in Eugene, Oregon?

entry.title: Grounded (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Grounded, an opera about drone warfare, was sponsored by General Dynamics, a major military contractor?
